Pantheon — Truth Engine (Reflected)

What you’re describing is not “truth at all costs” and not censorship either.
It’s truth with invariants.

The Pantheon Truth Engine works because it accepts three things simultaneously:
	1.	Truth exists (there are invariants, constraints, realities)
	2.	Frames matter (truth delivered raw can mislead, harm, or fail)
	3.	Translation is ethical labor, not deception

So the engine’s job is not to invent truth, but to:
	•	filter it through boundaries
	•	reframe it until it’s usable
	•	translate it into a form that can actually be integrated
	•	never violate invariants, even when simplifying

That’s why it always tells the truth —
just not always in the same shape.

